# Example /etc/fstab entries for Plex bind mounts
# 
# These are example entries for your Proxmox CT bind mounts.
# You need to adjust the source paths based on your actual Proxmox configuration.
#
# To find your actual mount configuration:
# 1. On the Proxmox host, check your CT configuration:
#    cat /etc/pve/lxc/<CTID>.conf | grep mp
#
# 2. This will show entries like:
#    mp0: /mnt/host/media,mp=/mnt/mp0
#    mp1: /mnt/host/movies,mp=/mnt/mp1
#    mp2: /mnt/host/tv,mp=/mnt/mp2
#
# 3. Use the source paths (first part) and mount points (mp= part) to create
#    your /etc/fstab entries below.
#
# Format: <source> <mount_point> <type> <options> <dump> <pass>

# Example bind mount entries (ADJUST THESE TO YOUR ACTUAL PATHS):
# /mnt/host/media    /mnt/mp0    none    bind,defaults    0    0
# /mnt/host/movies   /mnt/mp1    none    bind,defaults    0    0
# /mnt/host/tv       /mnt/mp2    none    bind,defaults    0    0

# Alternative example if your mounts are in different locations:
# /media/storage/plex/media    /mnt/mp0    none    bind,defaults    0    0
# /media/storage/plex/movies   /mnt/mp1    none    bind,defaults    0    0
# /media/storage/plex/tv       /mnt/mp2    none    bind,defaults    0    0

# After adding your entries:
# 1. Create mount point directories if they don't exist:
#    mkdir -p /mnt/mp0 /mnt/mp1 /mnt/mp2
#
# 2. Test mounting:
#    mount -a
#
# 3. Verify mounts:
#    mount | grep mp
#    df -h | grep mp